Recently we've removed the "Attach Screenshot" button from JIRA's issue view, however, our documentation has not been updated to reflect this change. Link to relevant documetation below:

https://confluence.atlassian.com/jira/attaching-a-screenshot-185729550.html

h3. Expected Behavior
Skip existing user and continue migrating other users, then display an "error summary" at the end of the process *or* add a validation to be performed before the migration starts.

h3. Actual Behavior
Directory migration is completely halted, leaving users in an inconsistent state, as migrated users will still be present on the Internal Directory, but without memberships.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Configure a "Delegated LDAP Authentication" directory;
# Enable the *Copy User on Login* option;
# Create an user with the same name as the one on LDAP in JIRA's Internal Directory;
# Move the Delegated directory to the top on *User Directories*;
# Login with the LDAP user;
# Try to migrate users from the Internal Directory to the Delagated;
# Until reaching the conflicting user, JIRA will import users normally. When it reaches that user, migration will be halted;

h3. Workaround
# Restore a backup from before the failed migration;
# Make sure the Delegated directory has no conflicting users;
# Perform the migration;

